wiki.content: On “Questions,” Chris Brown taps into his nostalgic side and interpolates Kevin Lyttle’s debut 2003 single “Turn Me On,” revamping the dancehall classic and putting his own spin on it. The track is part of Chris’ eighth studio album ‘Heartbreak on a Full Moon’ (2017). “Questions” was supposed to be released along with “Pills & Automobiles” in the first week of August following the success of earning two gold plaques for ‘Privacy’ and ‘Grass Ain't Greener’ and a platinum plaque ‘Party’ featuring Usher and Gucci Mane. However, due to setbacks with his record label, it was delayed in its release, despite a music video already being shot before “Pills & Automobiles” was released. The song leaked online a week before its actual release, though, with iTunes versions appearing online on August 11th. It’s believed that the track was prematurely released onto iTunes in select countries before being taken down. With these versions, the cover art was simply a black picture. Read more on Last.fm.
